title: Check for Apple XSAN, monitors stripe groups and storage pools.
agents: darwin
author: Jeremy Leggat <jleggat@asu.edu>
license: GPL
distribution:
description:
 This check makes use of the output of a working {cvadmin} on
 an OS X system. If the XSAN is properly configured and {cvadmin}
 is installed, then the agent will will output information about
 the stripe groups/storage pools used by this volume.

item:
 The name of the Volume and index number for each stripe group.

inventory:
 Stripe groups collects info for the storage pools associated with volumes on the system.
 stat, the general status of the volume.

perfdata:

examples:
